<span id="freeTextContainer12738177654764071117">Wow... <br/><br/>I absolutely loved this book. <br/><br/>Don&apos;t let the page length stop you from reading it! Despite its length, the story moves quickly and there&apos;s incredible tension throughout. There are a ton of characters to keep you interested (but not too many that you lose track) and who you&apos;ll want to scream at for doing the wrong thing or an incredibly awful thing. Some parts were breathtakingly tense and some parts were frightening. Don&apos;t think of this as a horror book with a monster... This is so much mo</span>
  <span id="freeText12738177654764071117" style="display:none">Wow... <br /><br />I absolutely loved this book. <br /><br />Don't let the page length stop you from reading it! Despite its length, the story moves quickly and there's incredible tension throughout. There are a ton of characters to keep you interested (but not too many that you lose track) and who you'll want to scream at for doing the wrong thing or an incredibly awful thing. Some parts were breathtakingly tense and some parts were frightening. Don't think of this as a horror book with a monster... This is so much more. The last 200 pages were a triumph IMO... <br /><br />Simply one of the best books I have ever read!<br /><br />PS: The actual ship was just found this past September. SO COOL! <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/north/hms-terror-found-1.3758400">http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/north/h...</a></span>
